 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2054<br> <font color=#333333>(10/6/02 3:00:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=65.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heal</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Calebe:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  The problem is Raz that in YOUR OPINOIN a new heal isn't needed.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Even better: I have <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>argued</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> that a new heal is not needed, and that a pet heal that was too good would be unbalancing.<br>
<br>
You have your opinion, to be sure, but really, where are your <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>arguments</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->?<br>
<br>
I have argued we have other options.  We do.  We have pet heals.  The epic can be chained three times.  Furthermore, just because you have your epic does not prevent you from casting other pets.  You can DS any pet after you cast it.  The options already exist.<br>
<br>
Your counter argument is that you refuse to chain the epic, and refuse to cast any other pet.  You <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>want</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> to heal instead.  Fine.  You want it.<br>
<br>
I have argued that the existing pet heals are adequate, and pointed at the existing mobs that epicked mages can already solo: Yeldema, Ice Burrowers, various 55+ mobs in Luclin.  <br>
<br>
Read <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessage?topicID=6925.topic">How fast can you AA EXP ?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> or <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showMessage?topicID=6924.topic">Do we overestimate our high end solo power?</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for examples of what people already solo with the epic using the existing pet heals.<br>
<br>
In contrast, you simply <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>claim</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> that the existing pet heal is inadequate, with no proof offered other than it is your opinion that it is inadequate.  How?  Why?<br>
<br>
You've failed to provide even one instance where the pet heal fails to allow you to solo a particular mob.  If it is inadequate, you should be able to name numerous examples where it fails.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> If mages can preserve their pets against strong mobs already with the existing heals, then exactly how are those heals inadequate?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Answer that.<br>
<br>
And yes, a 2000 pet heal for 500 mana <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>is</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;super pet heal&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>is</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> too good.  It has a better damage to mana ratio than any mage nuke, cannot be resisted, generates no aggro, and would almost always be preferable to a nuke.<br>
<br>
Refering to my earlier model for pet heals, a 2000 HP pet heal for the epic against a 70 DPS mob <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (like those found in Cazic Thule I believe)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would buy the pet nearly 30 seconds of fighting.  While back-to-back kilo-nukes would close the second gap by a comparable amount, it would generate much more aggro, and would not actually extend the life of the pet.  The advantage of heals over nukes, as demonstrated by <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Goladus</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is that by extending the life of a pet they allow time to cast additional spells.<br>
<br>
So what you are proposing is a heal that is better than every nuke we own or are ever likely to own.  And this for a class whose specialties includes nuking.<br>
<br>
If instead, we extrapolate from the existing pet heals, we get something like this:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Level 64ish, costs 500 mana, heals 1200 HP, 8.0 second cast time, 7.5 second recast.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Here is a spell with a 2.4 mana ratio, better than but consistant with our existing heals.  It is smaller than what would be our biggest nuke, just as the existing pet heals are.  It has advantages and disadvantages compared to nukes, and is not always clearly better.<br>
<br>
Oh, and as for speaking for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, here's a hint.  I have found it very useful when arguing in favor of improvements and upgrades for the mage class to try to see things from their point of view.  Much more compelling, I have found, if you can anticipate and counter all the various likely arguments.<br>
<br>
Much more compelling than <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;I want it because I want it and that is reason enough.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
